definition.value: A glycosyl alditol derivative consisting of an alpha-L-idopyranuronic acid residue and a 2,5-anhydro-4-O-sulfo-D-glucitol residue joined in sequence by a (1->3) glycosidic bond.
A glycosylfucose consisting of beta-D-galactopyranose and alpha-L-fucopyranose residues joined in sequence by a (1->4) glycosidic bond.
A glycosylmannose consisting of alpha-D-galactopyranose and beta-D-mannopyranose joined in sequence by a (1->6) glycosidic bond.
An amino disaccharide consisting of beta-D-galactopyranose and 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-D-galactopyranose residues joined in sequence by a (1->4) glycosidic bond.
A glycosyl alditol derivative consisting of beta-D-galactopyranose and N-acetyl-D-galactosaminitol joined in sequence by a (1->3) glycosidic bond.
A glycosyl alditol consisting of alpha-D-glucopyranose and D-galactitol residues joined in sequence by a (1->6) glycosidic bond.
A glycosylgalactose consisting of beta-D-galactofuranose and D-galactofuranose residues joined in sequence by a (1->3) glycosidic bond
